ouched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 150 should stop architecture churn and probe preprocessing on the strongest current small-K backbone: `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32, EF=16` with `USE_HADAMARD=1`.","`sparsify/config.py` currently exposes no configurable alternative loss function; the runtime-searchable non-architecture axes available without code changes are effectively `optimizer` and `use_hadamard`.","Hadamard already failed on routed K=16, so this run is specifically testing whether that was routing-specific; if bucketed K=32 also regresses clearly, deprioritize Hadamard preprocessing across the current EF=16 search lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If Hadamard improves the bucketed K=32 point, propagate the same preprocessing to K=64 to test whether the gain is a family-level coordinate-space effect rather than a K32-only artifact.","If Hadamard is neutral or worse but training is smooth, the next recipe probe should be an Adam retune on the same bucketed K=32 anchor with a materially lower LR rather than discarding optimizer exploration entirely from the old-LR failures.","If Hadamard regresses sharply again, treat preprocessing as effectively exhausted in the current launcher-exposed space and shift the next round to an optimizer-LR follow-up on the current bucketed anchor."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
